      • getHeartbeatDetails

        public <V> java.util.Optional<V> getHeartbeatDetails(java.lang.Class<V> detailsClass)
        Description copied from interface: ActivityExecutionContext
        Extracts heartbeat details from the last failed attempt. This is used in combination with retry options. An activity could be scheduled with an optional RetryOptions on ActivityOptions. If an activity failed then the server would attempt to dispatch another activity task to retry according to the retry options. If there was heartbeat details reported by the activity from the failed attempt, the details would be delivered along with the activity task for the retry attempt. The activity could extract the details by ActivityExecutionContext.getHeartbeatDetails(Class)() and resume from the progress.
        Specified by:
        getHeartbeatDetails in interface ActivityExecutionContext
        Parameters:
        detailsClass - type of the heartbeat details

      • doNotCompleteOnReturn

        public void doNotCompleteOnReturn()
        Description copied from interface: ActivityExecutionContext
